Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, low CO₂, and significant proteinuria, suggesting impaired renal function. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity, high protein, glucose, and ketones) further support possible nephropathy, with no evidence of infection. Low HbA1c and mild glucosuria may indicate recent hypoglycemia or altered glucose handling. Recommend nephrology evaluation and further assessment of renal and metabolic status.
